<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>France host Croatia in Tuesday night's UEFA Nations League action as group A3 leaders Portugal visit Sweden.</p>

<p>France bagan their campaign with a 1-0 victory over Sweden, courtesy of Kylian Mbappe's first-half goal at the Friends Arena in Solna. </p>

<p>Meanwhile Portugal recorded an emphatic 4-1 win over Croatia at Estádio Do Dragão, with Joao Cancelo opening the scoring with a thunderbolt, followed by goals from Diog Jota and Joao Felix. </p>

<p>Bruno Petkovic pulled one back in second-half stoppage time but Andre Silva netted a fourth with the lfinal kick of the game as Fernando Santos' side made a perfect start in Cristiano Ronaldo's absence. </p>

<p>Sportsmail's TOM CALDON will provide live Nations League coverage including score, lineups and build-up. </p>
